With two binary rules for $sqrt(2)$ and one for $phi.alt$, the binary alphabet presents a _plurality_ of admissible realisations, each optimising a different structural property. No single binary rule occupies every optimum at once. The trade-offs between compactness, stability, and depth remain distributed across distinct rules, and the musician working in a binary framework must choose which of these properties to prioritise. This plurality is specific to the binary case.

The ternary Padovan morphism $S arrow.r M, M arrow.r L, L arrow.r S M$, producing the plastic ratio $rho$, resolves this plurality. It is the _unique_ ternary rule that simultaneously satisfies every structural property available to its class: dynamical stability, ratio containment below the shuffle threshold $L slash S < 2$, minimum inflation within its admissibility class, and production of three geometrically related durations. Where the binary case distributes these properties across distinct rules, the ternary case consolidates them into one. This uniqueness is not a matter of convention or elegance but a consequence of a specific algebraic fact: there are no admissible stable substitutions of smaller inflation than the Padovan in the ternary range.#footnote[The technical formulation of this uniqueness is the _Pisot gap_ between $rho$ and the next Pisot number $psi approx 1.3803$: no real number between these two values can serve as the inflation of a stable substitution rule. See @sec:synthesis of Book IV for the derivation.] The move from two durations to three is therefore not a quantitative extension of the binary framework but a _qualitative consolidation_ of it: the binary tensions disappear at the ternary level, and a single rule occupies every admissible optimum.

This is the structure of the triad. Each irrational proportion is the unique solution to a different structural question. $sqrt(2)$ answers the question of the paired subdivision, and answers it twice: once with compactness, once with stability. $phi.alt$ answers the question of the solo binary recursion, with the unique combination of stability, minimal inflation, and maximal entropy. $rho$ answers the question of ternary consolidation, with the unique admissible three-duration rule. The three proportions are not three numbers that appear in three unrelated contexts; they are the three positions that are structurally forced once the substitution framework is taken seriously. They are what remains once the constraints are applied.

Two further consequences of this structure deserve brief mention before the framework is closed. First, the triad is _hierarchical_ in a specific sense: the three proportions ${sqrt(2), phi.alt, rho^2}$ stand in a near-progression, with $rho^2 approx 1.755$ exceeding $sqrt(2) approx 1.414$ and sitting comparably distant from $phi.alt approx 1.618$ on the other side. The swing feel each proportion supports is, correspondingly, distributed across the range: $sqrt(2)$ at the meantone of Section 3.2.3 (50% swing), $phi.alt$ at the medium-swing position of mainstream jazz, $rho^2$ at the heavier swing characteristic of the samba zone. The three proportions cover the useful range of rhythmic swing with structurally determined waypoints. Second, the triad opens onto a territory not yet mapped: the _quaternary_ case, with four distinct durations, and higher arities beyond. Whether the binary plurality reappears at quaternary, or whether the ternary uniqueness generalises to all arities above two, is an open question. The present sub-chapter stops at the ternary, and leaves the higher-arity territory as a direction for future work.

With the triad in place, the framework developed in this sub-chapter is complete in its essentials: three substitution rules, three irrational proportions, a structured family of fractal rhythms, and a principle that selects these objects from the space of possible substitutions. What remains is to state formally what a _fractal rhythm_ is — to extract from the preceding constructions the abstract object they have been pointing toward — and to examine the properties that follow from this definition. That is the task of the next section.